investigating our own experience isnt a matter of collecting more knowledge, its about looking over what we already think to be true and seeing its limitation
if anything, this server is a place to discuss the limits of philosophy and how they can never provide a wholistic answer to our problems
this server is about addressing the fundamental question ‚Äòwho am i?‚Äô which cannot be approached through any system, philosophy or dogma

we are just trying to understand why we cant be still with present experience
theres nothing new to learn about yourself in terms of thinking
so how am i to learn about the problem without having an opinion or theory about it?
because when you name your problem, that has to be a continuation of the past pattern. which is, action based off of ones preexisting knowledge
so can there be a complete opening up of the mind to learn something completely new?
and so a total change is never brought about as long as the mind sticks to its own path
whenever there is thought about the problem, that action must be limited to that specific domain of life
so we are trying to see if the mind can break away from this cycle
well you arent learning about the problem, the cycle of thought youre in can never learn anything new
the very act of naming is the act of putting off solving your problem
i hope you see that, its not pleasant but there it is
you dont need time to understand confusion. when you name it, youve put it off
yeah, like a robot. just pumping out the same ol output, saying things are good or bad and never giving care to listen
and so your attempt to meet it isnt total
because once youve identified the problem in thought, it is a fragment of the whole problem
no you cant name a thing and understand it
yeah, most people hear something then run it through their belief system and THEN understand the idea. but by that point is isnt an original idea, so no learning happens

and therefore it is a continuation of the old pattern

or theory

because that entire structure of thought is ‚Äòme‚Äô

what is unnecessary is the emotional relationship to that body of knowledge
so where thought is necessary is to understand what those words literally mean. you need a certain level of knowledge to even comprehend what the word ‚Äòweekend‚Äô means
and if its a conclusion about what i already know, then ofc im not learning about you
so an interpretation is thinking about what youre saying (which can only ever derive a conclusion from what i already know)
when i run off into an opinion about what youre saying, im now thinking about what my opinion is instead of what you‚Äôre directly telling me
and so if i think ‚Äòthats really great i wish i could do that‚Äô then ive tuned out of listening to you
so if youre telling me about an awesome experience you had on the weekend, an interpretation is a conclusion based off of my own personal experience about what youve told me
whether it is mechanical knowledge or self image, it is still thinking. lets be clear on that, theres no better or worse thinking
i want to be careful not to divide thought into correct and incorrect
however, if you are listening to a friend tell a story, you dont need to interpret
so we need thought to plan and write an essay, there needs to be knowledge about English
when you see what areas thought is necessary to function in, and what areas it is a hindrance
i mean interpretations like someone saying ‚Äòi went to a party on the weekend‚Äô and you immediately going ‚Äòi didnt go to a party, god i probably missed out im such a loser‚Äô
i dont just mean the linguistic factual understanding of the word -> ‚Äòcat‚Äô refers to a four legged mammal
sure but thats an automatic process, you need knowledge to understand a language and its grammatical conventions
you are engaging with your own thinking, which is not the actual communication
if you are interpreting something that is directly being spoken to you, you are no longer engaging with the communication
so your knowledge is still there, it only displays when it‚Äôs necessary
because youre keenly attentive to all their body language, words and expressions
so, when thought takes a backseat this actually allows subtlety to come into being
communication works the exact same way, you dont need to be thinking ‚Äòmy name is x‚Äô if someone says your name, you automatically understand someone is referring to you

for instance, if you drive, youve got heaps of knowledge about how it works but you dont need to think about the action because your action is automatically up to date with the most appropriate way to go about it
